# Learn JavaScript - Full Course for Beginners (freeCodeCamp)

**Video:** https://youtu.be/PkZNo7MFNFg
**Instructor:** Beau Carnes
**Source:** freeCodeCamp.org
**Format:** 134-part full JavaScript course for beginners

## 📌 About

This course teaches everything needed to get started with JavaScript, from
absolute basics to more advanced ES6+ concepts. It follows freeCodeCamp's
official JavaScript curriculum, so it pairs well with the interactive coding
challenges on their site.

## 🛠️ Installation & Setup

No special installation is required to start coding in JavaScript — it runs
directly in the browser.

1. **Text Editor**
   Install [VS Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/) (free) or any code editor of your choice.

2. **Browser**
   Use Chrome or Firefox. Open Developer Tools (`F12` or right-click → Inspect)
   and go to the **Console** tab to run JS instantly.

3. **Node.js (optional)**
   Install [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) if you want to run `.js` files from
   the terminal:
   ```bash
   node filename.js
   ```

4. **Practice Platform**
   Create a free account on [freecodecamp.org](https://www.freecodecamp.org/)
   to follow along with matching interactive coding challenges.

5. **Project Setup**
   Create a folder with an `index.html` file and a linked `script.js`:
   ```html
   <!DOCTYPE html>
   <html>
     <body>
       <script src="script.js"></script>
     </body>
   </html>
   ```

## 📚 Topics Covered

### 1. Fundamentals
- Introduction & running JavaScript
- Comments
- Variables (`var`, `let`, `const`)
- Assignment operators
- Basic math (add, subtract, multiply, divide, increment/decrement, decimals, remainders, augmented operators)

### 2. Strings
- Declaring strings
- Escaping quotes
- Concatenation (`+`, `+=`)
- String length & bracket notation
- String methods

### 3. Arrays
- Declaring, accessing, modifying arrays
- Array methods (`push`, `pop`, `shift`, `unshift`, `slice`, `splice`, etc.)
- Nested arrays

### 4. Functions
- Declaring functions
- Parameters & return values
- Global vs. local scope
- Functions working with arrays

### 5. Logic & Control Flow
- Booleans & comparison operators
- `if / else` statements
- Logical operators
- `switch` statements
- Loops (`while`, `for`, `do...while`)

### 6. Objects
- Declaring objects
- Accessing & updating properties
- Nested objects
- Objects vs. arrays

### 7. ES6+ / Advanced Topics
- `let` / `const` vs `var`
- Arrow functions
- Default parameters
- Rest & spread operators
- Destructuring
- Template literals
- Classes
- Modules
- Promises / async basics

### 8. DOM Manipulation
- Selecting elements
- Event listeners
- Dynamically updating the page

## ✅ How to Practice

